sfEzpdo symfony plugin
======================

Overview
--------

Ezpdo is a lightweight and easy-to-use persistence solution for PHP (see http://www.ezpdo.net/).

Installation
------------

This plugins does not include the ezpdo source code, so you have to install the ezpdo package
somewhere in your project (you can configure the ezpdo location - see configuration).

After installation, you can add the following configuration to your local `autoload.yml`
to enable Ezpdo autoloading:

  autoload:

    ezpdo_classes:
      name:           ezpdo autoloading
      files:
        epManager:    symfony/sfEzpdo/sfEzpdoAutoload.php

You can also include the `sfEzpdoAutoload.php` file in your actions.

Configuration
-------------

You can configure your ezpdo installation via the `databases.yml`:

  ezpdo:
    class:          sfEzpdoDatabase
    param:
      dsn:          mysql://username:password@localhost/dbname

To indicate your ezpdo installation path, add a `ezpdo_path` parameter to your `databases.yml`
configuration file.

By default, symfony will look for ezpdo under `lib/ezpdo`.

